review_blob: Nice looking beer, pitch black with dark brown head. Very rich in both nose and mouth, a bottle last for hours. Really stands out among its peers through a massive chocolate and chili finish. The heat from the chili is very apparent but still blend in nicely with the other flavors.
Pours pitch black with a brown head. A very nice beer with tonnes of flavor. A lot of character from the barrels with vanilla, bourbon, wood and chocolate. A light acidity from the roasted malts.

On tap at Bishop Arms Skvde. Hazy amber with thick medium seized head. Some floral hops but not that much, more focus on the malts with bread and cookie dough. Some sour off flavors, but they are in the background and not disturbing to much.

Red Amber color with a beige head. Piney hops in the focus along with some sweet cookie dough malty flavors as well as a touch of honey. A good bitterness balance the sweetness and lingers nicely. Some alcohol shines through. Altogether a nice beer but it dont feel so much like Christmas ;)

Golden to amber brew with a large white head. Malty sweet brew with candy sugar and nice warmth from the high ABV. Spicey belgian yeast along with some vanilla from the barrels makes it all a lot more interesting. Still not that heavy on the bourbon notes as expected.

Clear golden with a small white head. A nice well balanced beer with green apples, pears and herbs from the hops and medium malty sweetness with cookies and light bread. End with a good bitterness. This a good brew considering the 3,5 ABV.

Clear light golden with a small white head. Both the aroma and taste is focused on the hops that bring mango, orange, passion fruit and some tobacco. the malt very far in the background and itt very dry with a bitter ending, making it a perfect summer beer. Still, the lack of body makes it quite unbalanced.

Hazy amber/golden with a small off-white head that dissapears quickly. Earthy flavors with some wood along side fruity notes in both aroma and flavor. The is also some biscuits and cereal from the malts. Its fairly dry, got a somewhat watery mouthfeel and theres some metal notes turning up in the moderate bitterness.

Quite hazy golden beer with a nice dense head. Butter and grain in the aroma with a hint of licorice. The mouth goes along the same line with the light licorice making its appearance quite late along with a good bitterness. The beer is moderately sweet and fairly refreshing.

Slightly hazy with a light amber color. Low to medium sweet fruity, grassy and floral hops in both nose and mouth. A medium malty sweetness to balance the the quite subtle but still lingering bitterness. A quite low key brew that dont stand out in a good nor a bad way.

Clear amber with a white head. A quite low key beer with some fruity and floral hops and a medium malty base. Ends with a medium bitterness, the mouthfeel is a bit watery. Not to exiting IPA that I likely will not revisit in the near future.
Almost clear golden with a off-white head. A refreshing brew with peach, pine and caramel malt. A good bitterness at the end. A decent mid-range IPA and bbetter than the ratings IMO.
Clear amber with a white head. Very hoppy beer with tonnes of pine, honey and tropical fruits. A fairly good caramel malty sweetness as balance towards the solid bitterness.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Harvest Fresh Hop IPA - Southern Hemisphere

review_blob: Hazy amber with a large white head. Complex beer that have a balanced mix of malty sweetness, a bretty tartness and a bitter ending. This results in a full bodied yet refreshing brew.

Hazy golden with a medium white head. Very nice beer that is refreshing with the focus on the hops. Mainly peaches in the aroma and taste supported by some undefined citrus and tropical fruits. A long and bitter ending to finish it off.

Chestnut colored with a off-white head. It got the peppery and spicey aroma of a traditional saison but there is also a more untraditional caramel sweetness and touch of overdone popcorn, strange indeed. The taste is more within style although some extra caramel sweetness there as well.

This one has been sitting in the cellar for two three years. A dark ruby hazy brew that is quite turbid from all the yeast floating around. Very sweet vinous nose that I guess comes with age. The rich and intense taste is also sweet but is balanced by the high ABV and the fruity esters from the yeast. A very nice beer.

Hazy golden with a medium white head. A very refreshing beer that fits well in the summer. There is a lot of grapefruit and a solid bitterness that lingers. There is also a buttery taste from the malts.
Clear golden with a white head. Light bodied beer with some cereal and cockies. Some grassy hops and a good bitterness to finish it off. Quite refreshing and clean.

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Very hazy dark brown with absolutely no head what so ever. Looks almost like water with mud in it. This beer is hard to describe, its very rich and sweet with raisins, coffee, vanilla and port wine along side some smokey notes. Not that bitter ending but still well balanced towards the sweetness. A great beer I will surly revisit at earliest convenience...

Hazy golden with a medium white head. Very nice beer with a lot of hops that bring apricots, tropical fruits and piney notes. Also a light tobacco touch that I often find when the hops re fresh. There is also a good malty body that bring some sweetness and a very refreshing long lasting bitterness.
Hazy golden beer with a large white head. A lot of Belgian yeast and spices in both aroma and taste. A light orange touch as well and a good bitterness in the ending.
beer_name: Flying Dog In de Wildeman Farmhouse IPA

review_blob: Pale golden color that is quite hazy with large white frothy foam on top. A lot of flavors but still very refreshing, a key feature for a good saison. Plenty of Belgian yeast along with orange, apricots and undefined spices.

Pours pitch black with a medium mocca head. Very rich beer with tonnes of chocolate, coffee, vanilla and a fair amount of burnt notes. Quite vinous with raisins and a solid sweetness that is balanced by a good bitterness. Altogether very well balanced and very good imperial stout.

Clear golden with a small white head. This a very experimental brew, and experimental can be great, but here it went terrible wrong. I like apple pie a lot, but I dont want in in my beer. Heres plenty of apples and most of all a great deal of cinnamon. Its not sweet, but rather dry with a crisp bitterness in the end.

Hazy apricot color and a medium white head. A nice brew with a lot of hops in the aroma, taste and the lingering bitterness. The hops bring plenty of pine, tropical fruits and citrus notes. There is also a medium sweet body that balancing the bitterness.

Hazy golden beer with a medium white head. Quite boring brew with some hops but not at all enough. The body got some cookie notes but is not that exciting.  Also a strange chemical touch that is very present in the ending. A disappointment alright!

Hazy golden with a massive belgian style head. Lovely rich aroma with a lot of spices and yeast. The flavor contain the same features but with a disturbing amount of alcohol that bring down the overall impression a bit, still a nice beer.

Hazy dark golden with a medium white head. The aroma is very rich with a lot of caramel flavors. The hops bring a strange mix of over due tropical fruits and tobacco, still quite nice even if it dont sound like it. Quite good bitterness but perhaps to sweet in the end.

Pours hazy golden with a nice thick head. I dont really detect the pink pepper specifically, but there is a light spicy touch that might come from the pepper. Light body and medium hoppy with some earthy and citrus notes. Not that interesting in the end.
Clear amber with medium white head. Nice hoppy aroma with pine, pineapple and a lot very crisp citrus flavors. Medium sweet body that balance the bitterness nicely.
Clear amber with a white head. This beer is all about the roasted flavors of coffee and some chocolate. There is also a good bitterness to finish it of, but not so much hops in the flavor.

Slightly hazy golden with a off-white head. A lot of caramel sweetness and a fair amount of pine and pineapple from the hops, but still a little bit too old to have that really fresh hoppy touch. A good bitterness finnish it off.

Dark amber with a off-white head. Focus on the malts that bring caramel, cookie dough, cereal and light chocolate touch. But there is also a fair share of Herbal and floral hops. Ends with a smooth bitterness. A nice brew that is not extreme in any way, still stabil and well balanced.

Almost pitch black with a brown touch and a mocca head. There are a lot going on here, off course plenty of coffee, also dark chocolate, vanilla, wood, licorice and a soft feeling like someone pour soem double cream into the glass. A fairly rich acidity that disturbs a bit and it is not as full bodied as I like my Imperial Stouts.

Dark red amber with a off white head. Hoppy beer but still with sweet malty body. A good mix off pine, red berries, citrus and floral notes from the hops, together with a sweet cookie dough touch that balance the beer. Medium bitterness ends this quite nice brew, still it dont got fully the level of power I would like to have in a top of the line Strong ale.

Hazy golden with a large with head. Traditional Belgian flavors with yeast, subtitle spices and orange. It got a fairly sweet body, but still well balanced with a decent bitterness. Altogether a good Belgian style brew

Almost pitch black with absolutely no head. Roasted and sweet malty flavors in the centre. Also coffe and chocolate as expected but perhaps more licorice and a light touch of coca-cola. Since its a imperial stout, theres of course a decent punch to it, still not as powerful as I would like it to be.

Dark brown with a red touch and a mocca head. Coffee, chocolate, raisins, light acidity and light vanilla in both nose and mouth. Its better balanced in the aroma than in the flavor where it got slightly to much acidity. Ends with a quite light and smooth bitterness. A decent  porter but I expected more based on the ratings.
Dark dark brown with a hint off red and a almost non-existing light brown head. Nice coffee, prune and chocolate notes, still thinner than expected. Medium acidity and low bitterness.

Hazy golden with a medium white head. A medium malty DIPA with a lot of fruit, mainly pineapple,orange and grapefruit. The alcohol shines through more than I would like to. The flavors are all there, but not just tuned up as much as wanted. Altogether, a good but not extraordinary DIPA.
beer_name: Flying Dog Imperial IPA - Simcoe Single Hop

review_blob: A very hazy golden brew with a medium white head. A quite raw yeasty taste that I remind me of my homebrews. Some caramel malts and a lot of citric hops. A raw bitterness at the end.

Pitch black with a massive light brown head that disappears fairly quickly. A beer with huge flavors of coffee, chocolate, peat, leather, soil, raisins and a light acidity. A velvet mouthfeel with almost no carbonation. Altogether a very nice beer that got all the features Im after in an imperial stout.

Clear amber with a off-white head. Rich beer with focus on the caramel malt and a lot of honey. There is also some flowery hopps and also a touch. The bitterness is medium and balance the sweetness to some extent, still it come out quite sweet.

Dark dark brown with a amber touch and a thick light brown head. Very nice beer with a nice mix of chocolate, coffee, nuts alongside more flowery hoppy notes. Ends with a for the stile above average bitterness. A good porter that have a lot of flavor, yet its easy to drink and goes down like a charm.
Red orange with a huge off-white head. A very rich beer with a solid caramel malty body and tonnes of hops with orange, pine and tropical fruits.

Clear golden with a amber touch and a medium white head. Rich in both aroma and taste with the focus on the hoppy notes of pineapple, mango, peach and pine. It got a light sweetness and a good bitterness that lingers a while. A nice refreshing beer with a whole lot of fruity hop

Amber color with a medium off-white head. A very bland brew that do not really feel like an IPA, more a ESB if even that. It got a British touch with caramel and grassy, floral notes. Rich bitterness but it feel quite metallic and harsh.

Dark dark amber color with a light brown head. A very nice porter that is complex with a lot of flavors, still theres a lightness to it and it very easy to drink. A lot of coffee, especially in the aroma. There are also chocolate, some fruity hoppy notes and a light acidity in the back.
